        <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="nav-cta">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="container">

      <!-- HERO -->
      <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
        <div class="hero-main">
          <div class="trust-tag">
            <span class="trust-tag-icon">‚úì</span>
            TRUST BEFORE MONEY
          </div>

          <div class="hero-kicker">Private network ¬∑ Real agreements</div>
          <h1 id="hero-title">Structured lending, borrowing and investing between people.</h1>

          <p class="hero-subtitle">
            AmicBridge is a private network where people help each other with capital ‚Äì
            always with written agreements, clear expectations and realistic profit sharing.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-meta" aria-label="Key principles">
            <span><span class="dot"></span> No anonymous profiles</span>
            <span><span class="dot"></span> Agreements in plain language</span>
            <span><span class="dot"></span> No hidden fees or dark small print</span>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href="#contact" class="btn-primary">Talk to CEO</a>
            <a href="#how" class="btn-secondary">
              See how it works
              <span>‚Üò</span>
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-footnote">
            AmicBridge is not a bank. It is a structured way for people who trust each other
            to lend, borrow and co-invest with discipline and clarity.
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-side" aria-label="AmicBridge overview">
          <h3>AmicBridge in one look</h3>
          <div class="hero-pill-row">
            <span class="hero-pill"><strong>Written agreements</strong> for every action</span>
            <span class="hero-pill"><strong>Clear expectations</strong> on both sides</span>
            <span class="hero-pill"><strong>Transparent risk</strong> &amp; reward</span>
            <span class="hero-pill"><strong>Human-to-human</strong> network</span>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-stats">
            <div>
              <div class="hero-stat-label">Primary focus</div>
              <div>Trust networks, not mass markets</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="hero-stat-label">Design goal</div>
              <div>Less confusion, more clarity</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <!-- HOW & WHO -->
      <section class="section-cluster" aria-label="How AmicBridge works and who it is for">
        <article id="how" class="section-card">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">How it works</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Simple steps, strict discipline.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            No complex products. No hidden structures. Just clear agreements between people
            who choose to help each other ‚Äì with tools that make it hard to forget what was agreed.
          </p>

          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-label">Step 1</div>
              <div class="step-title">Define the relationship</div>
              <p>
                Is this a loan, an investment, or both? You agree up front on purpose,
                responsibilities and basic conditions.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-label">Step 2</div>
              <div class="step-title">Write it down</div>
              <p>
                Terms are written in clear language: amounts, timing, risk, profit sharing and
                what happens if life goes off-script.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-label">Step 3</div>
              <div class="step-title">Follow the agreement</div>
              <p>
                Agreement is stored, traceable and visible for the parties. People act like adults ‚Äì
                and can prove it later.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article id="who" class="section-card">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Who it is for</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">People who respect agreements.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            AmicBridge is not for everyone. It is for people who value trust, clarity
            and long-term relationships more than quick wins.
          </p>

          <ul class="who-list">
            <li>
              <span class="who-dot"></span>
              <span>Friends and family who want to help each other without destroying trust.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="who-dot"></span>
              <span>Small business owners who borrow from people they know.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="who-dot"></span>
              <span>Private investors who want clear, realistic agreements.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="who-dot"></span>
              <span>Community builders who prefer responsibility over anonymous platforms.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="badge-outline">
            Not a get-rich-quick system. A get-serious-about-agreements system.
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <!-- TRUST & CURRENCY -->
      <section class="section-cluster" aria-label="Trust model and currency handling">
        <article id="trust" class="section-card">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Trust & written agreements</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Trust first. Money second.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            Every action inside AmicBridge starts from trust ‚Äì but is captured in writing
            to protect both sides when memories fade or life changes.
          </p>

          <div class="trust-points">
            <div class="trust-point">
              <span class="trust-icon">üìù</span>
              <span>
                <strong>Clear terms.</strong> Amounts, dates, responsibilities and exits are written
                in plain language, not legal fog.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="trust-point">
              <span class="trust-icon">‚öñÔ∏è</span>
              <span>
                <strong>Balanced risk.</strong> Profit and risk are shared in a way that feels fair
                for both sides, not only the strongest party.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="trust-point">
              <span class="trust-icon">üìÇ</span>
              <span>
                <strong>Traceable agreements.</strong> Agreements can be revisited and referenced,
                so ‚Äúwe never talked about that‚Äù becomes rare.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="trust-point">
              <span class="trust-icon">üß©</span>
              <span>
                <strong>Life happens.</strong> You can build in what happens if things go wrong
                ‚Äì and treat that plan as part of the agreement.
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tag-row">
            <span class="tag">Respect before return</span>
            <span class="tag">Documentation by default</span>
            <span class="tag">No hidden conditions</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article id="currency" class="section-card">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Currency & units</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Designed to handle real-world money.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            The network will support relevant currencies and stable value units,
            depending on region, regulation and practicality.
          </p>

          <div class="split-row">
            <div class="split-card">
              <div class="badge-soft">Today</div>
              <h4>Local and standard currencies</h4>
              <p>
                Agreements can be expressed in commonly used currencies
                (for example NOK or EUR) and documented in simple numbers, not formulas.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="split-card" id="stablecoin">
              <div class="badge-soft">Direction</div>
              <h4>Stable, transparent value units</h4>
              <p>
                Long-term, AmicBridge aims to support digital units with stable value,
                backed by real agreements and real activity ‚Äì not pure speculation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

